article.headline: Quinnipiac 76, Wagner 72 (OT)
article.story: HAMDEN, Conn. (AP) -- Van Crafton had 20 points to lead Quinnipiac to a 76-72 overtime win against Wagner in Northeast Conference play Wednesday night. Crafton made 6-of-10 3-point attempts, including back-to-back threes in overtime to give Quinnipiac (10-13, 6-8) a four-point lead with 32 seconds left. Craig Benson added 18 points for Quinnipiac, making all 10 of his free throw attempts, including four in the final 20 seconds. Rob Monroe had nine points, seven assists and six rebounds for the Bobcats. Wagner (8-16, 7-8) was led by Sean Munson, who had 19 points and 15 rebounds. Mark Porter added 17 points, including a driving layup with 24 seconds left in regulation to tie the game at 63-63 and send it into overtime. Crafton missed a jumper as time expired in regulation. Wagner trailed by as many as 16 in the first half.
